          <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">Universitas Padjadjaran Street Feeding Animal Friend (UnpadSF) is a charity initiative founded by senior students of <strong> Faculty of Medicine and Faculty of Mathematics and Natural Sciences</strong> in 2021 for homeless community cats & dogs and promoting responsible pet ownership among students. <br><br> 
		  UnpadSF aims to:</p>
        </div>

		<ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 pl-5 text-lg text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
			<li class="pl-2">Provide humane care for stray cats and dogs, ensuring a healthy environment.</li>
			<li class="pl-2">Implement a Trap-Neuter-Return-Maintain (TNRM) program for population control.</li>
			<li class="pl-2">Educate the community about the role of free roaming cats and dogs in the ecosystem.</li>
		</ul>
  
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
		UnpadSF activities range from stray animal feeding, vaccination, rescues, Trap-Neuter-Return program, campaign, cat adoption programs & developing reflective collar as a product to promote pet safety. <br> <br>
		We're proud to be a part of creating a more compassionate culture and to continue building a better world for both human & animals.
		</p>
  
